remarks: Real number less-than is irreflexive.  Axiom for real and complex numbers, derived from set theory.  This restates ~ ax-pre-ltirr with ordering on the extended reals.  New proofs should use ~ ltnr instead for naming consistency.  (New usage is discouraged.)  (Contributed by Jim Kingdon, 15-Jan-2020.)
statement: axltirr $p |- ( A e. RR -> -. A < A ) $.
